5. If I execute docker exec -it nginx bash and then type exit, will the container stop? Why or why not?
Ans: Because docker exec starts a separate process inside an already running container. Exiting that process only terminates the Bash shell, not the container's main process. The container continues running as long as its main process (PID 1) is still running."
