Docker volumes are fully managed by Docker. They're stored in /var/lib/docker/volumes/. I don't need to worry about permissions or paths—Docker handles it.

Bind mounts directly map a host directory (like /data/sbi-reports) into the container. I have full control over the path, but I also have to manage permissions, SELinux, and ownership myself. For SBI, I would use volumes for my microservices because:
